The '''2004 Wyoming Cowboys football team''' represented the [[University of Wyoming]] in the [[2004 NCAA Division I-A football season]]. The Cowboys offense scored 318 points while the defense allowed 297 points. Led by head coach Joe Glenn, the Cowboys competed in the [[2004 Las Vegas Bowl|Las Vegas Bowl]]. ==Schedule== {{CFB Schedule Start|time=|rank=|ranklink=|rankyear=2004|tv=yes|attend=yes}} {{CFB Schedule Entry | date = September 4 | time = | w/l = w | nonconf = yes | away = | neutral = | rank = | opponent = [[2004 Appalachian State Mountaineers football team|Appalachian State]] | opprank = | site_stadium = [[War Memorial Stadium (Wyoming)|War Memorial Stadium]] | site_cityst = [[Laramie, WY]] | gamename = | tv = None | score = 53-7 | overtime = | attend = 13,205 }} {{CFB Schedule Entry | date = September 11 | time = 1:30 PM | w/l = l | nonconf = yes | away = y | neutral = | rank = | opponent = [[2004 Texas A&M Aggies football team|Texas A&M]] | opprank = | site_stadium = [[Kyle Field]] | site_cityst = [[College Station, TX]] | gamename = | tv = [[Fox Sports Net|FSN]] | score = 31-0 | overtime = | attend = 65,600 }} {{CFB Schedule Entry | date = September 25 | time = | w/l = w | nonconf = yes | away = | neutral = | rank = | opponent = {{cfb link|year=2004|team=Ole Miss Rebels|title=Mississippi}} | opprank = | site_stadium = [[War Memorial Stadium (Wyoming)|War Memorial Stadium]] | site_cityst = [[Laramie, WY]] | gamename = | tv = Ole Miss Pay-Per-View | score = 37-32 | overtime = | attend = 22,331 }} {{CFB Schedule Entry | date = October 2 | time = | w/l = w | nonconf = yes | away = | neutral = | rank = | opponent = {{cfb link|year=2004|team=ULM Warhawks|title=Louisiana Monroe}} | opprank = | site_stadium = [[War Memorial Stadium (Wyoming)|War Memorial Stadium]] | site_cityst = [[Laramie, WY]] | gamename = | tv = None | score = 37-10 | overtime = | attend = 12,125 }} {{CFB Schedule Entry | date = October 9 | time = | w/l = w | nonconf = | away = | homecoming 